<title>FRANCE: Accor to sign Carlson merger Jan 31.</title>
<headline>Accor to sign Carlson merger Jan 31.</headline>
<dateline>PARIS 1997-01-21</dateline>
<text>
<p>French hotel and travel group Accor said it would sign a deal to merge its business travel activities with Carlson Companies Inc into Carlson Wagonlit Travel on January 31.</p>
<p>The company made the announcement in an invite to a news conference by Accor's Jean-Marc Espalioux, Carlson's Marilyn Carslon-Nelson and Wagon-Lits' Jean-Marc Simon.</p>
<p>Accor and Carlson started to work together two years ago and there was nobody immediately available at the company to specify what the merger agreement would entail.</p>
